  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "- Azure cloud provider does not correctly handle failed calls to instance metadata endpoint. We currently handle transport errors but we don't handle response errors. Ref: https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/pkg/cloudprovider/providers/azure/azure_instance_metadata.go#L113\r\n\r\nwe should handle `resp.statusCode != 200`-- This currently yields into empty ip address assigned to node objects.\r\n\r\n- Remove the fall back to ARM once the above has been fixed. This removes the need for having identities in `azure.json` in case of `useInstanceMetadata = true`\r\n\r\n- Add `user-agent: golang/kubernetes` request header for all calls to instance metadata   \r\n\r\n- Cache the instance metadadata response and reuse for responding to `NodeAddress` and the rest of the calls. We can limit the call to `once per min` or even less.\r\n\r\n@kubernetes/sig-azure \r\n@feiskyer \r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`): `all`\r\n- Cloud provider or hardware configuration: `Azure`\r\n- OS (e.g. from /etc/os-release): `Ubuntu xenial`\r\n- Kernel (e.g. `uname -a`): `all`\r\n- Install tools: `all`\r\n- Others:\r\n\r\n<!-- DO NOT EDIT BELOW THIS LINE -->\r\n/king bug",
